Navamsha Application Privacy Policy
Last updated: 26 August 2024
Introduction
Navamsha L.L.C-FZ ("we", "us", "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your personal information when you use our mobile application, Navamsha (the "App"), which provides astrological insights, personalized content, and other related services. By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of your personal information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
Personal Data We Collect
When you use the App, we collect email address, birth information (date of birth, time of birth and place of birth), device location to provide you with a personalized experience and to deliver our services effectively. We only collect the personal data necessary to provide you with the features and services of our App, and we ensure that your data is handled securely and responsibly.
How We Collect and Use Personal Data
We collect your personal data using user input and device data sharing permissions to ensure a seamless and secure user experience. Your personal data is used for user account management, personalization of in-app content and marketing communications. By using your personal data for these purposes, we aim to provide you with an enjoyable, personalized, and secure experience while using our App.
Sharing Your Personal Data
We collaborate with select third-party service providers to enhance the features and functionality of our App. In doing so, we may share app usage statistics with third parties like Google Analytics, Firebase, Appsflyer and others. We never share your birth data with anyone and keep this information confidential.
Managing Your Personal Data
To ensure your control over your personal data, we provide options to access, modify, or delete your date of birth, time of birth, place of birth, and device location through the Settings section within the App.
Security Measures
We take the security of your personal data seriously and implement a range of modern security technologies to safeguard your information. By employing it, we strive to protect your personal data from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction, while maintaining the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of our services.
Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We employ cookies and various tracking technologies provided by third-party platforms to enhance your experience with our App and website, personalize our marketing communications, and analyze the effectiveness of our advertising efforts.
User-Generated Content and Conduct
We gather and utilise user-generated content, including comments, reviews, and ratings on the App Store and Google Play. This content may be incorporated into our advertisements, marketing materials, or used to enhance our services.
To maintain a respectful and secure environment, we enforce the following guidelines for user conduct:
Unauthorised access: Any attempts to hack, manipulate, or modify the App code are not allowed. We are committed to ensuring a secure and fair experience for all users.
Intellectual property: Publishing or sharing the App's files and code on any websites, platforms, or media without our express permission is forbidden. We protect our intellectual property rights and ask that users respect them as well
Third-Party Websites and Services
Our App may include links to third-party websites or services that are not under our control. We are not responsible for the privacy practices, content, or policies of these external sites or services. We strongly recommend that you review the privacy policies of any third-party websites or services you access via our App to ensure you understand how your data may be collected, used, and shared by these entities.
By providing these links, we do not endorse or guarantee the privacy practices of these third parties. It is your responsibility to safeguard your personal data when visiting or interacting with external sites or services connected to our App.
International Data Transfers
Your personal data may be transferred to, stored in, and processed in countries other than your country of residence, as part of our global operations and the use of third-party service providers. These countries may have different data protection laws and standards than those in your country of residence. By using the App, you consent to the transfer of your personal data to countries outside of your country of residence.
We take appropriate measures to ensure that your personal data is protected and treated securely in accordance with this Privacy Policy and applicable data protection laws, regardless of the country in which it is processed. This includes implementing suitable contractual clauses and safeguards with our third-party service providers to maintain the confidentiality and integrity of your personal data.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. Your continued use of the App following the posting of changes constitutes your acceptance of such changes. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.
Contact Us
If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding your personal data or related to data protection laws, please contact us by email at
hi@navamsha.com